41/*!
42 * \class CEmptyMap
43 * \brief We use this dummy class instead of std::map when
44 * we only need the enum definition and not the string to
45 * enum maps, this makes compilation much faster.
46 */
47template <typename T, typename U>
48struct CEmptyMap {
49 CEmptyMap(std::initializer_list<std::pair<const T, U> >) {}
50};
51
52#ifdef ENABLE_MAPS
53template<class T, class U>
54using MapType = std::map<T,U>;
55#define MakePair(a,b) {a,b},
56#else
57template<class T, class U>
58using MapType = CEmptyMap<T,U>;
59#define MakePair(a,b)
60#endif

156/*!
157 * \brief Get the number of faces of the element.
158 * \param[in] elementType - element type
159 * \return number of faces
160 */
161inline unsigned short nFacesOfElementType(unsigned short elementType) {
162 switch (elementType) {
163 case LINE: return N_FACES_LINE;
164 case TRIANGLE: return N_FACES_TRIANGLE;
165 case QUADRILATERAL: return N_FACES_QUADRILATERAL;
166 case TETRAHEDRON: return N_FACES_TETRAHEDRON;
167 case HEXAHEDRON: return N_FACES_HEXAHEDRON;
168 case PYRAMID: return N_FACES_PYRAMID;
169 case PRISM: return N_FACES_PRISM;
170 default: assert(false && "Invalid element type."); return 0;
171 }
172}
173
174/*!
175 * \brief Get the number of points of the element.
176 * \param[in] elementType - element type
177 * \return number of points
178 */
179inline unsigned short nPointsOfElementType(unsigned short elementType) {
180 switch (elementType) {
181 case LINE: return N_POINTS_LINE;
182 case TRIANGLE: return N_POINTS_TRIANGLE;
183 case QUADRILATERAL: return N_POINTS_QUADRILATERAL;
184 case TETRAHEDRON: return N_POINTS_TETRAHEDRON;
185 case HEXAHEDRON: return N_POINTS_HEXAHEDRON;
186 case PYRAMID: return N_POINTS_PYRAMID;
187 case PRISM: return N_POINTS_PRISM;
188 default: assert(false && "Invalid element type."); return 0;
189 }
190}

461 RUNTIME_ADJFLOW_SYS = 6, /*!< \brief One-physics case, the code is solving the adjoint equations is being solved (Euler and Navier-Stokes). */

965/*!
966 * \brief Associate turb models with their family
967 */
968inline TURB_FAMILY TurbModelFamily(TURB_MODEL model) {
969 switch (model) {
970 case TURB_MODEL::NONE:
971 return TURB_FAMILY::NONE;
972 case TURB_MODEL::SA:
973 return TURB_FAMILY::SA;
974 case TURB_MODEL::SST:
975 return TURB_FAMILY::KW;
976 }
977 return TURB_FAMILY::NONE;
978}

1018/*!
1019 * \brief Function to parse SST options.
1020 * \param[in] SST_Options - Selected SST option from config.
1021 * \param[in] nSST_Options - Number of options selected.
1022 * \param[in] rank - MPI rank.
1023 * \return Struct with SST options.
1024 */
1025inline SST_ParsedOptions ParseSSTOptions(const SST_OPTIONS *SST_Options, unsigned short nSST_Options, int rank) {
1026 SST_ParsedOptions SSTParsedOptions;
1027
1028 auto IsPresent = [&](SST_OPTIONS option) {
1029 const auto sst_options_end = SST_Options + nSST_Options;
1030 return std::find(SST_Options, sst_options_end, option) != sst_options_end;
1031 };
1032
1033 const bool found_1994 = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::V1994);
1034 const bool found_2003 = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::V2003);
1035 const bool found_1994m = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::V1994m);
1036 const bool found_2003m = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::V2003m);
1037
1038 const bool default_version = !found_1994 && !found_1994m && !found_2003 && !found_2003m;
1039
1040 const bool sst_1994 = found_1994 || found_1994m;
1041 /*--- Default version since v8. ---*/
1042 const bool sst_2003 = found_2003 || found_2003m || default_version;
1043
1044 /*--- When V2003m or V1994m is selected, we automatically select sst_m. ---*/
1045 const bool sst_m = found_1994m || found_2003m || default_version;
1046
1047 const bool sst_sust = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::SUST);
1048 const bool sst_v = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::V);
1049 const bool sst_kl = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::KL);
1050 const bool sst_uq = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::UQ);
1051
1052 if (sst_1994 && sst_2003) {
1053 SU2_MPI::Error("Two versions (1994 and 2003) selected for SST_OPTIONS. Please choose only one.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1054 } else if (sst_2003) {
1055 SSTParsedOptions.version = SST_OPTIONS::V2003;
1056 } else {
1057 SSTParsedOptions.version = SST_OPTIONS::V1994;
1058 }
1059
1060 // Parse production modifications
1061 if ((int(sst_v) + int(sst_kl) + int(sst_uq)) > 1) {
1062 SU2_MPI::Error("Please select only one SST production term modifier (VORTICITY, KATO-LAUNDER, or UQ).", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1063 } else if (sst_v) {
1064 SSTParsedOptions.production = SST_OPTIONS::V;
1065 } else if (sst_kl) {
1066 SSTParsedOptions.production = SST_OPTIONS::KL;
1067 } else if (sst_uq) {
1068 SSTParsedOptions.production = SST_OPTIONS::UQ;
1069 }
1070
1071 SSTParsedOptions.sust = sst_sust;
1072 SSTParsedOptions.modified = sst_m;
1073 SSTParsedOptions.uq = sst_uq;
1074 return SSTParsedOptions;
1075}

1115/*!
1116 * \brief Function to parse SA options.
1117 * \param[in] SA_Options - Selected SA option from config.
1118 * \param[in] nSA_Options - Number of options selected.
1119 * \param[in] rank - MPI rank.
1120 * \return Struct with SA options.
1121 */
1122inline SA_ParsedOptions ParseSAOptions(const SA_OPTIONS *SA_Options, unsigned short nSA_Options, int rank) {
1123 SA_ParsedOptions SAParsedOptions;
1124
1125 auto IsPresent = [&](SA_OPTIONS option) {
1126 const auto sa_options_end = SA_Options + nSA_Options;
1127 return std::find(SA_Options, sa_options_end, option) != sa_options_end;
1128 };
1129
1130 const bool found_neg = IsPresent(SA_OPTIONS::NEG);
1131 const bool found_edw = IsPresent(SA_OPTIONS::EDW);
1132 const bool found_bsl = !found_neg && !found_edw;
1133
1134 if (found_neg && found_edw) {
1135 SU2_MPI::Error("Two versions (Negative and Edwards) selected for SA_OPTIONS. Please choose only one.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1136 }
1137
1138 if (found_bsl) {
1139 SAParsedOptions.version = SA_OPTIONS::NONE;
1140 } else if (found_neg) {
1141 SAParsedOptions.version = SA_OPTIONS::NEG;
1142 } else {
1143 SAParsedOptions.version = SA_OPTIONS::EDW;
1144 }
1145 SAParsedOptions.ft2 = IsPresent(SA_OPTIONS::FT2);
1146 SAParsedOptions.qcr2000 = IsPresent(SA_OPTIONS::QCR2000);
1147 SAParsedOptions.comp = IsPresent(SA_OPTIONS::COMP);
1148 SAParsedOptions.rot = IsPresent(SA_OPTIONS::ROT);
1149 SAParsedOptions.bc = IsPresent(SA_OPTIONS::BC);
1150
1151 /*--- Validate user settings when not in experimental mode. ---*/
1152 if (!IsPresent(SA_OPTIONS::EXP)) {
1153 const bool any_but_bc = SAParsedOptions.ft2 || SAParsedOptions.qcr2000 || SAParsedOptions.comp || SAParsedOptions.rot;
1154
1155 switch (SAParsedOptions.version) {
1156 case SA_OPTIONS::NEG:
1157 if (!SAParsedOptions.ft2 || SAParsedOptions.bc)
1158 SU2_MPI::Error("A non-standard version of SA-neg was requested (see https://turbmodels.larc.nasa.gov/spalart.html).\n"
1159 "If you want to continue, add EXPERIMENTAL to SA_OPTIONS.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1160 break;
1161 case SA_OPTIONS::EDW:
1162 if (any_but_bc || SAParsedOptions.bc)
1163 SU2_MPI::Error("A non-standard version of SA-noft2-Edwards was requested (see https://turbmodels.larc.nasa.gov/spalart.html).\n"
1164 "If you want to continue, add EXPERIMENTAL to SA_OPTIONS.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1165 break;
1166 default:
1167 if (SAParsedOptions.bc && any_but_bc)
1168 SU2_MPI::Error("A non-standard version of SA-BCM was requested (see https://turbmodels.larc.nasa.gov/spalart.html).\n"
1169 "If you want to continue, add EXPERIMENTAL to SA_OPTIONS.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1170 break;
1171 }
1172 }
1173 return SAParsedOptions;
1174}

1221 SULUKSNA, /*!< \brief Kind of transition correlation model (Suluksna). */

1230/*!
1231 * \brief Structure containing parsed LM options.
1232 */
1233struct LM_ParsedOptions {
1234 LM_OPTIONS version = LM_OPTIONS::NONE; /*!< \brief LM base model. */
1235 bool LM2015 = false; /*!< \brief Use cross-flow corrections. */
1236 TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::DEFAULT;
1237};
1238
1239/*!
1240 * \brief Function to parse LM options.
1241 * \param[in] LM_Options - Selected LM option from config.
1242 * \param[in] nLM_Options - Number of options selected.
1243 * \param[in] rank - MPI rank.
1244 * \return Struct with SA options.
1245 */
1246inline LM_ParsedOptions ParseLMOptions(const LM_OPTIONS *LM_Options, unsigned short nLM_Options, int rank, TURB_MODEL Kind_Turb_Model) {
1247 LM_ParsedOptions LMParsedOptions;
1248
1249 auto IsPresent = [&](LM_OPTIONS option) {
1250 const auto lm_options_end = LM_Options + nLM_Options;
1251 return std::find(LM_Options, lm_options_end, option) != lm_options_end;
1252 };
1253
1254 LMParsedOptions.LM2015 = IsPresent(LM_OPTIONS::LM2015);
1255
1256 int NFoundCorrelations = 0;
1257 if (IsPresent(LM_OPTIONS::MALAN)) {
1258 LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::MALAN;
1259 NFoundCorrelations++;
1260 }
1261 if (IsPresent(LM_OPTIONS::SULUKSNA)) {
1262 LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::SULUKSNA;
1263 NFoundCorrelations++;
1264 }
1265 if (IsPresent(LM_OPTIONS::KRAUSE)) {
1266 LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::KRAUSE;
1267 NFoundCorrelations++;
1268 }
1269 if (IsPresent(LM_OPTIONS::KRAUSE_HYPER)) {
1270 LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::KRAUSE_HYPER;
1271 NFoundCorrelations++;
1272 }
1273 if (IsPresent(LM_OPTIONS::MEDIDA_BAEDER)) {
1274 LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::MEDIDA_BAEDER;
1275 NFoundCorrelations++;
1276 }
1277 if (IsPresent(LM_OPTIONS::MEDIDA)) {
1278 LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::MEDIDA;
1279 NFoundCorrelations++;
1280 }
1281 if (IsPresent(LM_OPTIONS::MENTER_LANGTRY)) {
1282 LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::MENTER_LANGTRY;
1283 NFoundCorrelations++;
1284 }
1285
1286 if (NFoundCorrelations > 1) {
1287 SU2_MPI::Error("Two correlations selected for LM_OPTIONS. Please choose only one.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1288 }
1289
1290 if (LMParsedOptions.Correlation == TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::DEFAULT){
1291 if (Kind_Turb_Model == TURB_MODEL::SST) {
1292 LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::MENTER_LANGTRY;
1293 } else if (Kind_Turb_Model == TURB_MODEL::SA) {
1294 LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::MALAN;
1295 }
1296 }
1297
1298 return LMParsedOptions;
1299}

2053/*!
2054 * \brief Return true if format is one of the Paraview options.
2055 */
2056inline bool isParaview(OUTPUT_TYPE format) {
2057 switch(format) {
2058 case OUTPUT_TYPE::PARAVIEW_ASCII:
2059 case OUTPUT_TYPE::PARAVIEW_LEGACY_BINARY:
2060 case OUTPUT_TYPE::SURFACE_PARAVIEW_ASCII:
2061 case OUTPUT_TYPE::SURFACE_PARAVIEW_LEGACY_BINARY:
2062 case OUTPUT_TYPE::PARAVIEW_XML:
2063 case OUTPUT_TYPE::SURFACE_PARAVIEW_XML:
2064 case OUTPUT_TYPE::PARAVIEW_MULTIBLOCK:
2065 return true;
2066 default:
2067 return false;
2068 }
2069}
2070
2071/*!
2072 * \brief Return true if format is one of the Tecplot options.
2073 */
2074inline bool isTecplot(OUTPUT_TYPE format) {
2075 switch(format) {
2076 case OUTPUT_TYPE::TECPLOT_ASCII:
2077 case OUTPUT_TYPE::TECPLOT_BINARY:
2078 case OUTPUT_TYPE::SURFACE_TECPLOT_ASCII:
2079 case OUTPUT_TYPE::SURFACE_TECPLOT_BINARY:
2080 return true;
2081 default:
2082 return false;
2083 }
2084}
